<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-08-19T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-08-19T07:00:00-05:00" n="98" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d98">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00 R 296/522: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Kellogg</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-08-19T13:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">August 19,
                                        1924—1 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received August 19—8:38
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>359. Young canceled his sailing reservations for tomorrow. He will go to
                            Paris and work out plan of reparations as Agent General. I think that it
                            will be arranged to carry out your original program for his temporary
                            appointment to start the Dawes Plan in operation. He hopes that
                            arrangement as to permanent Agent General may be reached as soon as
                            possible.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>